roportional to the white dwarf mass, which could explain\nvarious aspects of the diversity of Type Ia supernovae, such as their variation\nin brightness, the dependence of their mean luminosity on the host galaxy type,\nand the weak correlation between ejecta velocity and peak brightness.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Feb 2005 10:41:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
